Title: Remarks on Duffin-Kemmer-Petiau theory and gauge invariance

Authors: J. T. Lunardi, B. M. Pimentel, R. G. Teixeira and J. S. Valverde (Sao

Paulo, IFT)Comments: 19 pages, no figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. A268 (2000) 165-173

Two problems relative to the electromagnetic coupling of Duffin-Kemmer-PetiauHamiltonian form of the theory and the apparent difference between theInteraction terms in DKP and Klein-Gordon (KG) Lagrangians. For this, we firstdiscuss the behavior of DKP field and its physical components under gaugetransformations. From this analysis, we can show that these problems simply donot exist if one correctly analyses the physical components of DKP field.